Package: cawCV
Title: Cluster-Aware Cross-Validation Partitioning for Repeated-Measures
    Predictors
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Joseph",
           family = "Hagan",
           email = "jlhagan@bcm.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3285-2131"))
Description: Cluster-aware cross-validation partitioning for clinical
    prediction models with repeated-measures predictors and subject-level
    binary outcomes. Three partitioning strategies are provided: naive
    observation-level k-fold, subject-level k-fold, and leave-one-cluster-out.
    Pre-validation diagnostic functions report per-predictor intraclass
    correlation and within-subject lag-1 autocorrelation to characterise
    within-subject dependence before a partitioning strategy is chosen. The
    partitioning functions return fold assignments only and are agnostic to
    the modelling method and performance metric used downstream.
